c26a520c-1f8e-41a3-8e69-f6b91f83420c.title: Roavar
c26a520c-1f8e-41a3-8e69-f6b91f83420c.text:
Greetings traveller. Welcome to 'The Hair Of The Dog'
Tavern. What can I do you for?

14e2c0fc-f5a0-4e21-ac9a-2bff0166b402.title: Roavar
14e2c0fc-f5a0-4e21-ac9a-2bff0166b402.text:
Well, I dunno... The village is kind of on the fringe out
here, I dunno how up to date the stuff I hear about
is..

options.text: Tell me about the land of Morytania.
Tell me about the shopkeepers here.
Tell me about the temple to the West.

be81206d-bb5c-4f99-bb3c-9a4fd4b1f668.title: Roavar
be81206d-bb5c-4f99-bb3c-9a4fd4b1f668.text:
You want to know about Canifis? I dunno why, not a
lot happens here. We're just your typical everyday
down at earth werewolf folk, after all...

adfaaa8c-c547-4bd5-9b8c-22b4304ed35c.title: <player>
adfaaa8c-c547-4bd5-9b8c-22b4304ed35c.text: So... everyone here is a werewolf?

da26abdf-048b-49af-a2e9-f67331267462.title: Roavar
da26abdf-048b-49af-a2e9-f67331267462.text: Yep. We are as Zamorak made us!

ca982c8f-143a-432f-a924-a1b5b2cc2ef0.title: Roavar
ca982c8f-143a-432f-a924-a1b5b2cc2ef0.text:
Yeah, he's great isn't he? Every year we hold a big
festival to give thanks to Zamorak for keeping us well
fed and happy here.

5a7ce86b-9093-4785-97be-b56cd662b40a.title: Roavar
5a7ce86b-9093-4785-97be-b56cd662b40a.text:
I hear over in the West they worship Saradomin, but I
dunno why! What's he ever done to help out us
werewolves, huh?

ebd43003-3637-4140-bfe7-c227131ef491.title: Roavar
ebd43003-3637-4140-bfe7-c227131ef491.text:
I hear he has all these crazy followers who say things
like we shouldn't kill people and eat them! What's up
with that?

23b9ad62-5869-465d-ba64-37ea077daa44.title: Roavar
23b9ad62-5869-465d-ba64-37ea077daa44.text:
Aaaah, not for a good few months yet. Come and ask
me again nearer to the time, I'll keep some extra meat
and mead back from the rest for ya pal.

eadf835f-69db-431f-ab14-915921cb9660.title: Roavar
eadf835f-69db-431f-ab14-915921cb9660.text:
Well that's my speciality! The local brew's named
'Moonlight Mead' and will set you back 5 gold.
Whaddya say? Fancy a pint?

240dc899-92d7-4f75-bbaa-2d06fdd314e0.title: Roavar
240dc899-92d7-4f75-bbaa-2d06fdd314e0.text:
Eh, suit yourself. You're missing out on a genuine
taste experience.

94b5dc38-a9b5-4003-b401-c5964aee218e.title: <player>
94b5dc38-a9b5-4003-b401-c5964aee218e.text:
I don't have the money on me right now though... can
I start a tab?

e3f0d94c-8ddc-4107-8134-5a09f5c95e39.title: Roavar
e3f0d94c-8ddc-4107-8134-5a09f5c95e39.text: You see that sign behind me there?

994537e7-da4b-4a89-a764-f54e632e1c72.title: <player>
994537e7-da4b-4a89-a764-f54e632e1c72.text:
The one that says; 'Please Do Not Ask For Credit As
Being Attacked By A Large Angry Werewolf Inn
Keeper Often Offends'?

fe306629-4943-4073-863c-b3e89499ae73.title: <player>
fe306629-4943-4073-863c-b3e89499ae73.text: Tell me about the land of Morytania.

337a06b3-c2c7-4b64-baa9-e47e5357ecf8.title: Roavar
337a06b3-c2c7-4b64-baa9-e47e5357ecf8.text:
Well, I don't know what to tell you really... This village
is called Canifis and lies on the border between
Morytania and Misthalin... so we're kind of on the front
line if those Saradominists to the west ever decide to

513489f4-350d-4225-9e90-b499fcfe845a.title: Roavar
513489f4-350d-4225-9e90-b499fcfe845a.text:
attack us... South East of here is the castle of Lord
Drakan, our master.

fb9f95d2-aee2-4dee-a006-2a2880f29636.title: Roavar
fb9f95d2-aee2-4dee-a006-2a2880f29636.text:
Ahhh... you must be new to these parts if you haven't
heard of Lord Drakan! He's the lord of this land, and
we all pledge allegiance to him.

03a7d4ed-c9c1-48a2-b532-6060f689fb2f.title: Roavar
03a7d4ed-c9c1-48a2-b532-6060f689fb2f.text:
In return for our allegiance, and the tithe of course, he
keeps our land safe from any invaders and the
Saradominists who want to kill us all.

e8fad365-9261-4b16-923d-39249fe73306.title: Roavar
e8fad365-9261-4b16-923d-39249fe73306.text:
Ah, well, in return for his protection, we have to give
Lord Drakan a share of blood every week. If we don't
have any to spare from our hunts, then we need to
pick a member of the village to give their life in return

96cd2004-cb82-4979-80ff-c4a01943765c.title: Roavar
96cd2004-cb82-4979-80ff-c4a01943765c.text: for the blood so that the tithe is fulfilled.

f76a1696-811d-4a99-84f5-d532e1b72539.title: <player>
f76a1696-811d-4a99-84f5-d532e1b72539.text:
You mean you kill someone you know in order to meet
the tithe???

2b4f10da-00ea-454b-b5ad-aed1929e153f.title: Roavar
2b4f10da-00ea-454b-b5ad-aed1929e153f.text:
That's right, but only if we haven't managed to get
enough spare blood from our hunts. It's kind of severe
if you look at it that way, but frankly, I think the price
is fair in return for his protection and his tolerance of

86163128-fc98-4a52-b630-eb3e6e87be7b.title: Roavar
86163128-fc98-4a52-b630-eb3e6e87be7b.text:
our village. He could probably kill us all if he wanted us
gone, so keeping on his good side is worth the sacrifice
to us. Lucky we're not human really!

17ae54ef-d2e5-4549-a5ae-19c4d08a67e1.title: Roavar
17ae54ef-d2e5-4549-a5ae-19c4d08a67e1.text:
He hates humans! Apparently long ago his brother
Draynor was trapped in Misthalin and lost much of his
powers, and was recently killed by some human!

8a3b4d7e-a62c-4916-b661-5aa7cbff6150.title: Roavar
8a3b4d7e-a62c-4916-b661-5aa7cbff6150.text:
Man, I'd hate to be a human around here, that's for
sure. Drakan would really enjoy hunting them down
and killing them!

c29514a4-500e-4c36-98a6-59d61e1d3aa1.title: <player>
c29514a4-500e-4c36-98a6-59d61e1d3aa1.text: Tell me about the temple to the west.

942b6684-726e-4ba9-8a23-7c3a33f23379.title: Roavar
942b6684-726e-4ba9-8a23-7c3a33f23379.text:
Well, I'm not old enough to remember the full story
behind it, but it was a terrible day for our kingdom
when it was built there.

4980be08-cc2b-42d0-b62d-35930a6f7ffd.title: Roavar
4980be08-cc2b-42d0-b62d-35930a6f7ffd.text:
Apparently Morytania had a once strong kingdom, with
lands spreading far further west than they do today,
and south into the desert, until the day when a sneak
attack by the hated human forces who worship

4a8ddcbb-6a67-4462-9c82-33a76cd3cefa.title: Roavar
4a8ddcbb-6a67-4462-9c82-33a76cd3cefa.text:
Saradomin burned our villages and slaughtered our
peoples in mass.

4c496da4-7154-4667-bea6-97ed86024e03.title: Roavar
4c496da4-7154-4667-bea6-97ed86024e03.text:
They then cursed the river, so that it would burn our
kind should we touch it! Can you imagine??? To make
an entire river poisonous to us???

ba1135a9-c9da-450a-b102-7a7ed3ddaf1f.title: Roavar
ba1135a9-c9da-450a-b102-7a7ed3ddaf1f.text:
Luckily they seem to have calmed down somewhat
recently, and tend to stay on their side of the river...
but the wrong they have done my people will never be
forgotten, and will never be forgiven. What is worse is

6a2ffedc-9a98-4ad0-983a-bed99fc6b3ec.title: Roavar
6a2ffedc-9a98-4ad0-983a-bed99fc6b3ec.text:
that they then had the nerve to build that gigantic
statue on the river mouth to mock the slaughter of our
people and the poisoning of our river! I can understand
Lord Drakan's hatred for them even if I do not share

674ff134-8512-4ecb-881d-19fc71497080.title: Roavar
674ff134-8512-4ecb-881d-19fc71497080.text:
Absolutely! If I ever met one I would gobble him up
where he stands! And then chew the bones for dessert!

afac74d9-df27-465e-97a1-5be03a866999.title: <player>
afac74d9-df27-465e-97a1-5be03a866999.text: Tell me about the shopkeepers here.

97d66381-2e03-460a-9af9-9330e42f0c13.title: Roavar
97d66381-2e03-460a-9af9-9330e42f0c13.text:
Hmmm? Why, who did you want to hear the gossip
about?

562ca9c4-dcff-4de1-91ca-e861954bd093.title: Roavar
562ca9c4-dcff-4de1-91ca-e861954bd093.text:
A story??? Heh, well the only one I can think of right
now is one my dear old mammy told me as a pup...

87a2315d-5414-4c07-8ece-53409a22a8ee.title: Roavar
87a2315d-5414-4c07-8ece-53409a22a8ee.text: Now how did it go... Ah yes!

45e0908b-ad59-4119-a57b-cf8e8da96bad.title: Roavar
45e0908b-ad59-4119-a57b-cf8e8da96bad.text:
Once upon a time a brave young wolf was walking
through a forest, when he came upon a human dressed
all in red. 'Aha!' he thought to himself, 'Here's a nice
easy meal!' But the human talked to him, and as he was

fcaa44c7-ef64-4ce9-9294-61cad38cc02d.title: Roavar
fcaa44c7-ef64-4ce9-9294-61cad38cc02d.text: always taught to be a polite wolf, he spoke back to it.

f6c7e821-2345-4161-b8b7-8910b3681180.title: Roavar
f6c7e821-2345-4161-b8b7-8910b3681180.text:
Well, this cunning human told him that there was a
better meal that would not run away in a house in the
woods. As the brave young wolf could see that this
human was not fully grown, he figured maybe he'd

536a5b71-afc1-4233-92b0-fa10d78235f0.title: Roavar
536a5b71-afc1-4233-92b0-fa10d78235f0.text:
better get a better meal at this house, so he ran as fast
as his paws could carry him to the house the human
told him about... inside he found an old human lying in
bed, and although the meat was a little tough, as the

52aaef49-4397-4288-a70d-b825eaa23669.title: Roavar
52aaef49-4397-4288-a70d-b825eaa23669.text:
human was older than he thought, he had a good meal
and decided to sleep it off in the house for awhile. He
had not been asleep long though, when he was woken by
a knocking at the door. The human in red had followed

16fb491c-b318-41d9-b36a-b25a2cb4d66b.title: Roavar
16fb491c-b318-41d9-b36a-b25a2cb4d66b.text:
him to the house! Suspecting a human trap, the brave
young wolf put on the old humans clothes and jumped
into the bed, so that he could pretend to be human and
escape from this terrible trap! Well now, this human

34b3100b-f3b8-41a6-8501-b537abf532cd.title: Roavar
34b3100b-f3b8-41a6-8501-b537abf532cd.text:
dressed in red came into the house, and pretended to
believe the brave wolf was really a human, and began to
talk to him. But then the human started asking strange
questions of the wolf, because the human knew that it

bac5347b-95a2-4d30-9b29-a8a563e6d239.title: Roavar
bac5347b-95a2-4d30-9b29-a8a563e6d239.text:
was not a human at all! The brave young wolf decided
to try and escape, for it was only a young human, and
not very strong, so the brave young wolf said he would
eat the human if they did not let him escape! As he said

e576c3c2-92cf-46a2-93d6-f46981e8c3d8.title: Roavar
e576c3c2-92cf-46a2-93d6-f46981e8c3d8.text:
this however, the human in red shouted out at him:
'Aha! You are a wolf!' and as the human shouted this
another bigger human ran into the room from outside!
This bigger human was much stronger and was

fd2fc305-a2d4-4e74-8b4a-36f687c5e48e.title: Roavar
fd2fc305-a2d4-4e74-8b4a-36f687c5e48e.text:
carrying an axe, and the poor young wolf died in this
terrible trap made for him by the humans.

ef52290a-5d53-4609-8b47-a389d4e17370.title: Roavar
ef52290a-5d53-4609-8b47-a389d4e17370.text: And do you know what the moral of this story is?

0ed661e3-8299-431d-a6a1-0f7948193645.title: Roavar
0ed661e3-8299-431d-a6a1-0f7948193645.text:
It's 'Never trust humans' of course! My dear old
mammy told me that story when I was a pup, and I'm
still alive and well to tell it to you today!

92a88ffe-5672-4aaa-a070-ef5c51bb498b.title: <player>
92a88ffe-5672-4aaa-a070-ef5c51bb498b.text: Um... yeah. It was great. Really.

90a177cc-0484-40b5-ad8d-b8d3cc988df4.title: <player>
90a177cc-0484-40b5-ad8d-b8d3cc988df4.text:
I bet you have some juicy gossip about Fidelio the
general store owner.

2b524bf6-e156-453a-b1aa-8a365598288f.title: Roavar
2b524bf6-e156-453a-b1aa-8a365598288f.text:
That nut job? Oh sure, we all know about him. He was
a real firebrand daredevil when he was younger, always
taking risks to make himself a quick buck... he got
himself caught up in the smuggling trade, sneaking over

c7e1f095-2241-4378-aa3f-c7d78587138d.title: Roavar
c7e1f095-2241-4378-aa3f-c7d78587138d.text:
the border into Misthalin and pretending to be a human
so he could buy exotic items to sell.

39de0f54-e0c2-4fda-9bd1-3b70101df01b.title: Roavar
39de0f54-e0c2-4fda-9bd1-3b70101df01b.text:
Oh man, you name it! Flour... buckets... tinderboxes...
chisels... he could get the lot! He's been doing it so long
now though, his nerves are shot.

e7fb1a22-14e6-4fcc-ad0f-27939020bd07.title: <player>
e7fb1a22-14e6-4fcc-ad0f-27939020bd07.text: Exotic items? From Misthalin? Like what?

518630ad-3f29-4426-b566-c740dfd83e35.title: Roavar
518630ad-3f29-4426-b566-c740dfd83e35.text:
Nowadays he's a disgrace, he can barely string a
sentence together and jumps at his own shadow. Makes
you feel ashamed to be a werewolf.

0aff3fea-a286-4a18-88af-812d8a9bc82a.title: <player>
0aff3fea-a286-4a18-88af-812d8a9bc82a.text: Got anything to share about Barker the clothes seller?

b20b7044-3951-4229-9709-c00d21088bb5.title: Roavar
b20b7044-3951-4229-9709-c00d21088bb5.text:
Eh, I don't like the guy much, but you can't knock the
quality of his stock. They're some fine quality threads
you can get yourself there.

d1e01a5a-546a-41ca-b826-667f77cdbd46.title: Roavar
d1e01a5a-546a-41ca-b826-667f77cdbd46.text:
Eh... I can't really tell you to be honest. Something
about the guy just gets my hackles up everytime he
opens his yap, know what I mean?

2c333f4d-737e-4f6b-be6b-a2c73ec0908e.title: Roavar
2c333f4d-737e-4f6b-be6b-a2c73ec0908e.text:
Lucky for you. I can't really explain it, I just don't like
the guy. Does great clothes though, you got to give him
that.

0cb1232f-ae13-4f44-8cb2-7f2675155768.title: <player>
0cb1232f-ae13-4f44-8cb2-7f2675155768.text: Know anything interesting about Rufus the food seller?

41a2bbce-ca3d-4139-9b48-0d6a0cbe4a00.title: Roavar
41a2bbce-ca3d-4139-9b48-0d6a0cbe4a00.text:
Ah yeah... good old Rufus... He's kind of getting on in
years and doesn't like to come out of his wolf form so
often, but let me tell you this: that guy is a hunter
through and through. You seen how much food he

5c640621-c147-4724-888f-08073d7eb2ce.title: Roavar
5c640621-c147-4724-888f-08073d7eb2ce.text:
catches a day? That takes real dedication! Some of the
young pups think just because a wolf has a bit of grey
in his fur then he's past it, but I've seen him put those
pups to shame in a hunt! He's a real inspiration to us

22cb4bf4-5e63-4352-8453-0be0117f9151.title: <player>
22cb4bf4-5e63-4352-8453-0be0117f9151.text: Tell me what you know about Sbott the Tanner.

b1b38cee-f192-4907-8c5f-ce0360e521cb.title: Roavar
b1b38cee-f192-4907-8c5f-ce0360e521cb.text:
Hey, I won't hear a word said bad about that guy! He's
an honest and hard-working wolf if I ever met one! He
charges a lot for his job, but he's one of the best
tanners I've ever seen - and I'm over four hundred

a9452546-ba8b-4e74-a62e-40c66d92d65f.title: Roavar
a9452546-ba8b-4e74-a62e-40c66d92d65f.text: years old! You need stuff tanning, I recommend him!

d1201024-f8c1-4be8-b91d-8c6011ab9e75.title: Roavar
d1201024-f8c1-4be8-b91d-8c6011ab9e75.text:
...I don't know why you talked to me if you don't want
anything then...
